args: Phew! That was a close one.\nAre you all right, Ilia?
Yeah, thanks to you. But what are you\neven DOING here?
I kept thinking about you. Going after\nkidnappers is dangerous work and all.
Yeah, basically... I'd been looking around\nfor you, and then what do I see when I\nfinally find you? You in big trouble!
Oh, she's the one from back in town...\nIs she a friend of yours, Ilia?
Yep. Her name's Nino. Nino, this is\nMordecai. He's my...my family.
Thank you for saving Ilia.\nAlso, your wing is beautiful.
Yeah, what's up with that, anyway?
Ack! I didn't mean to leave it out!\nSo that's...um... Geez, how to explain?
I was just so desperate to help my friend\nthat I...
Hey, that's explanation enough for me.\nThanks for the assist, Nino.
Welp, thanks to Nino, we managed to\ndefeat all those lousy kidnappers.
Now you kids really ARE safe,\nso let's go home for real.
Why are they crying, Ilia? Aren't they safe?
They were probably too scared to cry\nuntil just now.
Don't worry, kiddos. Those bad guys\nwon't ever bother you again.
*sniff* There's no Saint Starfall, is there?
But then he turned into a scary man!
And when we asked where he went,\nthe scary man said he was all made up.
I was trying to be good for him, but...
They said everyone was lying about Saint\nStarfall giving us presents! WAAAAAAH!
Kidnapping is bad enough, but did they\nhave to crush their dreams while they\nwere at it?
Easy, children. The Saint Starfall you saw\nin this place was false.
No! You're a liar like all the other\ngrown-ups!
Yeah, you can't fool us again!\nThere's no Saint Starfall!
There IS a Saint Starfall, and he's gonna\nKEEP bringing presents to all the good\nchildren like he always has!
Liar! You're a big, fat, smelly liar!
Okay, that seems unnecessary. Also,\nhow about you wait until tomorrow\nmorning before calling me a liar?
Remember how the lady at the Church said\nSaint Starfall sees when you're good?
All of you are good kids who didn't let\nthe bad men scare you at all.
You bet your bunions he will!\nNow go home and get some rest already.
Mordecai, can you take these kids home?
Of course. But what about you?
I've got something I have to take care of.\nI'll meet you back at the inn once I've got\nit all sorted out.
Are you sure everything will be all right?
You told those kids Saint Starfall was real.\nHeck, you practically had ME believing it.
Oh, that? Yeah, that's not a problem.\nI'm just gonna be Saint Starfall myself.
Should be obvious enough—I'm gonna\nthrow some presents together and then\nhand-deliver 'em to their houses.
But it's already dark, and most of\nthe shops are closed.
Then we just have to find some that stay\nopen late or beg the others to reopen.
Why would you go so far for a pack of\nchildren you don't even know?
Because there's nothing worse than\ndenying a kid's possibilities.
Nothing good comes from crushing\ndreams—you gotta grow those puppies!
And as an alchemist, I'm going to keep\nshowing everyone new possibilities.
Because that's going to lead to\na better future.
It's the same thing with Saint Starfall.
Telling them that Saint Starfall MIGHT\nexist will make their tomorrow so much\nmore fun than just admitting he doesn't.
Us adults shouldn't deny them that.\nWe shouldn't rob them of their choices.
So it sounds like you DO have a choice.\nAnd all of them are equally valid.
Please allow me to help, Ilia. I would\nalso like to become Saint Starfall.
Oh man, that'd be GREAT! This'll be so\nmuch easier with you helping out!
Now let's go prove that\nSaint Starfall's real!
